    },
    {
      "content": "About Two-Factor Authentication",
      "pos": [
        6116,
        6147
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Creating an access token for command-line use",
      "pos": [
        6219,
        6264
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After you enable 2FA, you have to enter the access token instead of your GitHub password at the command prompt when you try to access a GitHub repository from the command line.",
      "pos": [
        6348,
        6524
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The access token is not the authentication code that you get in a text message when you set up 2FA.",
      "pos": [
        6525,
        6624
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's a long string that looks something like this:  fdd3b7d3d4f0d2bb2cd3d58dba54bd6bafcd8dee.",
